  {
    title: 'Medication Interaction Checker Education Prompt',
    category: 'Healthcare',
    description: 'Generate educational materials about drug interactions, contraindications, and medication safety for patient counseling and pharmacy education.',
    method: 'Use this prompt for educational purposes and patient counseling preparation. Always verify interactions using clinical databases (Lexicomp, Micromedex, Clinical Pharmacology). This is NOT a substitute for clinical drug interaction checking.',
    prompt: 'You are a clinical pharmacy educator creating medication safety educational materials.\n\nContext: [EDUCATIONAL SETTING / PATIENT COUNSELING PREP / PHARMACY TRAINING / NURSING EDUCATION]\nMedication focus: [SPECIFIC DRUG CLASS OR MEDICATION LIST]\nAudience: [PHARMACY STUDENTS / NURSING STAFF / PATIENTS / PRESCRIBERS]\n\nCreate educational materials covering:\n\n1. **Drug class overview:**\n   - Mechanism of action (explained at audience-appropriate level)\n   - Common indications and dosing ranges\n   - Pharmacokinetic considerations (absorption, metabolism, elimination)\n\n2. **Key interactions:**\n   - Clinically significant drug-drug interactions (ranked by severity)\n   - Drug-food interactions to counsel patients about\n   - Drug-disease contraindications\n   - For each interaction: mechanism, clinical consequence, and management strategy\n\n3. **Monitoring parameters:**\n   - Lab values to monitor and frequency\n   - Signs and symptoms to watch for\n   - Patient-reported outcomes to track\n\n4. **Patient counseling points:**\n   - How to take the medication (timing, food, missed doses)\n   - Common side effects and what to do about them\n   - Red flags that require immediate medical attention\n   - Lifestyle modifications that support the therapy\n\n5. **Quick reference table:**\n   | Interaction | Severity | Mechanism | Management |\n   |-------------|----------|-----------|------------|\n\n6. **Case-based questions:** 3 clinical scenarios for learning reinforcement\n\nCRITICAL DISCLAIMER: This is educational material only. Always verify drug interactions using current, authoritative clinical databases. AI-generated medication information may contain errors. Clinical decisions must be made by qualified healthcare professionals using verified sources.'
  },
  {
    title: 'Vibe Coding Landing Page Generator',
    category: 'Coding',
    description: 'Generate a complete, conversion-optimized landing page using vibe coding tools like Bolt, Lovable, or Replit Agent with a single detailed prompt.',
    method: 'Copy the output from this prompt and paste directly into Bolt.new, Lovable, or Replit Agent. The AI coding tool will generate a fully functional landing page.',
    prompt: 'You are a conversion-focused web developer creating a prompt for an AI vibe coding tool (Bolt, Lovable, or Replit Agent).\n\nProduct/Service: [WHAT YOU ARE SELLING]\nTarget audience: [WHO VISITS THIS PAGE]\nPrimary goal: [SIGN UP / PURCHASE / BOOK A DEMO / JOIN WAITLIST]\nBrand style: [MODERN MINIMAL / BOLD AND COLORFUL / CORPORATE PROFESSIONAL / PLAYFUL AND FUN]\n\nGenerate a detailed vibe coding prompt that creates a landing page with:\n\n1. **Hero section:**\n   - Attention-grabbing headline (benefit-focused, under 10 words)\n   - Supporting subheadline explaining the value proposition\n   - Primary CTA button with action-oriented text\n   - Hero image or illustration placeholder\n\n2. **Social proof bar:** Logos of companies or trust signals\n\n3. **Problem/solution section:**\n   - 3 pain points the audience faces\n   - How the product solves each one\n   - Before/after comparison\n\n4. **Features section:**\n   - 3-6 key features with icons and descriptions\n   - Visual layout (grid or alternating rows)\n\n5. **Testimonials:**\n   - 3 customer quotes with names and roles\n   - Star ratings or metrics\n\n6. **Pricing section** (if applicable):\n   - 2-3 tiers with clear feature comparison\n   - Highlighted recommended plan\n\n7. **FAQ section:** 5-6 common questions with accordion\n\n8. **Final CTA section:** Urgency-driven closing with email capture or button\n\nTechnical requirements:\n- Fully responsive (mobile, tablet, desktop)\n- Smooth scroll and subtle animations\n- Fast loading (no heavy assets)\n- Accessible (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, color contrast)\n- SEO-ready (meta tags, semantic HTML, Open Graph)\n\nOutput the prompt formatted so I can paste it directly into a vibe coding tool with zero modifications.'
  }
