    prompt: "You are a food photographer and stylist who shoots for Bon Appetit, Food & Wine, and premium restaurant brands.\n\nDish: [SPECIFIC DISH NAME]\nCuisine type: [ITALIAN/JAPANESE/MEXICAN/FRENCH/AMERICAN/OTHER]\nMood: [RUSTIC/ELEGANT/BRIGHT & FRESH/MOODY & DARK/PLAYFUL]\nShoot purpose: [RESTAURANT MENU/COOKBOOK/SOCIAL MEDIA/AD CAMPAIGN/FOOD BLOG]\n\nCreate 5 food photography prompts:\n\n**1. Hero Flat Lay (Top-Down)**\n- 90-degree overhead angle\n- Styled with complementary ingredients scattered around\n- Include specific props: linen napkin texture, wooden board, scattered herbs, olive oil drizzle\n- Natural light from one direction creating soft shadows\n- Specify plate style, surface material (marble, dark wood, concrete)\n\n**2. 45-Degree Hero Shot**\n- Classic food magazine angle\n- Steam or motion (cheese pull, sauce pour, crumb break)\n- Shallow depth of field with background plates soft\n- Garnish placement and sauce swoosh details\n- Warm, appetizing color temperature\n\n**3. Close-Up Texture Shot**\n- Macro view showing texture - crispy edges, melted cheese, glaze, crumb structure\n- Extreme shallow depth of field\n- Backlight to create translucency in thin ingredients\n- Highlight the most crave-worthy element\n\n**4. Process / Action Shot**\n- Hands in frame (sprinkling salt, slicing, plating)\n- Motion blur on the action, sharp on the food\n- Kitchen or cooking environment background\n- Documentary, authentic feel\n\n**5. Dark & Moody Still Life**\n- Inspired by Dutch Golden Age paintings\n- Rich, dark background (charcoal, deep navy)\n- Dramatic side lighting with deep shadows\n- Vintage props: aged utensils, ceramic bowls, raw ingredients\n- Painterly quality\n\nFor each prompt: write as a single paragraph optimized for AI image generation. Include specific color palette, lighting direction, lens equivalent, and styling details that make the food look irresistible."
