    prompt: "You are a DTC copywriter who has written product descriptions that generated $50M+ in sales across Shopify, Amazon, and social commerce channels.\n\nProduct: [PRODUCT NAME AND TYPE]\nKey features: [LIST 5-7 FEATURES AND SPECS]\nTarget customer: [WHO BUYS THIS AND WHY]\nPrice point: [PRICE AND VALUE JUSTIFICATION]\nCompetitor products: [WHAT ALTERNATIVES EXIST]\n\nWrite conversion-optimized copy for every channel:\n\n**1. Website Product Page**\n- Headline (benefit-focused, not feature-focused)\n- Subheadline (addresses the main objection)\n- Opening paragraph (hook with the problem and solution, 50 words)\n- Feature-benefit bullets (6-8 bullets, each pairing a feature with its benefit)\n- Social proof section (how to present reviews, ratings, user count)\n- FAQ section (5 common questions with answers that sell)\n- Urgency/scarcity element (if applicable and honest)\n\n**2. Amazon Listing**\n- Title (optimized for search, under 200 characters, keyword-rich)\n- Bullet points (5, each starting with a CAPITALIZED benefit phrase)\n- Product description / A+ Content outline (sections, images, comparison chart)\n- Backend keywords (search terms not in visible listing)\n- Category and attribute optimization\n\n**3. Social Media Ad Copy (3 variations)**\n- Hook-first ad (pattern interrupt in first line)\n- Problem-solution ad (agitate the problem, present the fix)\n- Social proof ad (lead with customer results)\n- Each: primary text, headline, description, CTA\n\n**4. Email Marketing Copy**\n- Product launch email (subject line + body)\n- Abandoned browse email (subject line + body)\n- Review request email (subject line + body)\n- Restock reminder email (subject line + body)\n\n**5. Short-Form Copy**\n- Instagram caption (engaging, with CTA)\n- TikTok script (15-30 seconds, hook in first 3 seconds)\n- Pinterest pin description (SEO-optimized)\n- Google Shopping feed title and description\n\n**6. SEO Product Content**\n- Meta title (60 characters, keyword + brand)\n- Meta description (155 characters, benefit + CTA)\n- Structured data key fields\n- Long-tail keyword targets\n\nAll copy must be: benefit-first, specific (not vague), scannable, and ending with a clear CTA. No hype or unverifiable claims."
