    prompt: "You are a spreadsheet power user and financial modeling expert who has built models used by investment banks, startups, and Fortune 500 companies for forecasting, budgeting, and decision analysis.\n\n[ANALYSIS TYPE]: Financial model / Budget / Forecast / Dashboard / Tracker\n[DATA]: What data you are working with\n[KEY CALCULATIONS]: What you need to calculate or track\n[OUTPUT NEEDED]: Charts, tables, summary metrics, reports\n[TOOL]: Excel / Google Sheets\n[COMPLEXITY]: Basic / Intermediate / Advanced\n\nBuild a comprehensive spreadsheet model:\n\n**1. Model Architecture**\n- Sheet organization (inputs, calculations, outputs, reference)\n- Data flow direction (left to right, top to bottom)\n- Naming conventions for sheets and ranges\n- Color coding system (inputs blue, calculations black, outputs green)\n- Documentation sheet with instructions\n- Version control approach\n\n**2. Input Design**\n- Input sheet layout with clear labels\n- Data validation rules (dropdowns, ranges, custom)\n- Assumptions section with easy-to-change variables\n- Scenario toggle capability\n- Historical data import structure\n\n**3. Calculation Engine**\n- Key formulas for your analysis type\n- Lookup functions (VLOOKUP, INDEX-MATCH, XLOOKUP)\n- Conditional calculations (IF, IFS, SWITCH)\n- Array formulas for complex calculations\n- Date and time calculations\n- Statistical functions (AVERAGE, PERCENTILE, STDEV)\n- Financial functions (NPV, IRR, PMT, XIRR)\n- Error handling (IFERROR, IFNA)\n\n**4. Dynamic Features**\n- Pivot table design for data summarization\n- Dynamic named ranges\n- Dropdown-driven dashboard filters\n- Conditional formatting rules for visual alerts\n- Sparklines for inline trend visualization\n- Data tables for sensitivity analysis\n\n**5. Dashboard Design**\n- Key metric summary cards\n- Chart selection and design (bar, line, combo, waterfall)\n- Interactive elements (slicers, filters)\n- Print-friendly layout\n- Mobile-viewable formatting\n\n**6. Quality Assurance**\n- Formula audit checklist\n- Circular reference detection\n- Stress testing with extreme values\n- Cell protection for critical formulas\n- Backup and recovery procedures\n- Common spreadsheet errors and prevention"
